column10:
I LOVE the story, the plot, the world, the design of creatures, the setting, the fact that you find "modern world" stuff with overgrown nature on them, the factions/tribes!

BUT THE COMBAT SUCKS BALLS!
-hitboxes are janky (enemies sometimes run in your general direction and stunlock you as a result);
-FORGET about ever using melee! you'll get stunlocked (or at least take like 60% damage in a single hit) if you try to melee; and trying to finish downed/stunned enemies usually does LESS damage than shooting arrows in a weakpoint you probably can't see or is covered in armor;
-you can't even time your melee attacks, you have to button mash, and that results in the above point;
+WEAKNESSES! That's literally the only reason the combat would ever be enjoyable! There's elements and weakpoints on enemies that are kinda fun to break off, but the fact that melee is literally not an option because of all this, kinda makes the combat boring;
+if you like stealth, this game is a stealth game; encounters take so much less time and frustration if you just stealth whenever you can
-UNLESS THE PROMPT DISAPPEARS RIGHT WHEN YOU CLICK IT AND YOU FUCKING ATTACK INSTEAD OF STEALTH-TAKEDOWN-ING, ALERTING EVERYONE IN A 5KM RADIUS (the range is not an issue; exaggerating for the funny)

I will finish this because I'm curious how things go and the exploration is actually fun, but it is SO DAMN FRUSTRATING because everything hits REALLY HARD on just the normal difficulty, stunlock is prevalent (but only against you), and the hitboxes are super janky

the most fun 100% i have done:"]
everything in this game is just super well done:}
cant wait for n forbidden west ;)
